<br>
Warriors don't need more DPS right now, if anything a few classes should be throttled back (more than) a bit... we do need better mitigation (i.e. functional AC), avoidance (shields will help if done right), HP, and improved taunt.<br>
<br>
Mitigation fixes will probably have to wait until PooPoo ships, and it's questionable if they'd be retroactive (previous ones weren't).  <br>
<br>
Avoidance adjustments/improvements could be from items/shields IF they are done correctly and don't horribly imbalance knight/caster/monks (i.e. item based AND close control of which classes can use them!).  <br>
<br>
More hp = always good (by item stat or effect, AA, or innate), and STOP ADDING 0.0 WEIGHT ALL/ALL items with &gt; ~30hp!.  <br>
<br>
Warrior taunt could be totally fixed just by doing the following:<br>
-fails = adds as much hate as ranger snare/pally stun/SK debuff.<br>
-succeeds = works like it does not.<br>
<br>
Pallys, rangers, and SKs can basically chaincast FAST (~ taunt recycle delay) super low mana spells to maintain aggro, even if they are totally resisted, AND can channel through damage... making failed taunts aggro as much as those skills would eliminate that particular, hopefully unintended, benefit.  Obviously it'd be a bad idea to add that to THEIR taunt however...<br>
<br>
RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uabsoreq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AbsorEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Messenger of the gods</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/02 6:23:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=82>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://everquest.station.sony.com/images/absor.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Shield of the Slain Unicorn...</span><hr size=1> &quot;I don't think warriors would have an issue with giving up a lot of dps for better mitigation. The block skill would obviously be a huge boon to warriors, or any tank class, and damage mitigation on a shield would be very nice as well. It does no good however, if we can't hold aggro as well or better than we do now.&quot;<br>
