Granted these are high end weapons but you get my point. Godly ratio 1hs are not available to warriors... therefor our ability to maintain aggro while wielding a shield is loosly based on luck and lousy at best.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Let me point out something:<br>
<br>
Warrior<br>
Offense 252<br>
1 handed slashing 250<br>
1 handed blunt 250<br>
<br>
Paladin<br>
Offense 225<br>
1 handed slashing 225<br>
1 handed blunt 225<br>
<br>
That is a greater than 100 atk difference.<br>
<br>
If you compare those 2 weapons, the raw ratio on the dawncaller is a little less 30% better. If you look at speed, the AHB is 15% faster, which translates into the DB being applied 15% more often. Factor in the atk difference and I wouldn't be surprised if the damage output difference between a paladin using dawncaller and a warrior using ONLY an AHB in mainhand wouldn't be very big. I wouldn't want to place bets on who did the most damage, because it would vary depending on which mob they are fighting. High AC mobs I would say the warrior wins. DB applied more often = more damage. Low AC xp mobs, my guess would be the paladin by a very tiny amount. <br>
<br>
<br>
Below is a comparison. It ignores double attack and haste (haste is irrelevant, it scales evenly) and ignores procs.<br>
The first listing is a 24/22 equipped paladin.<br>
<br>
The second listing is a 16/19 equipped warrior.<br>
<br>
Max theoretical DPM<br>
(24 * 5.7) + 11 = 148 every 2.2 seconds, 4036 max possible DPM - 100%<br>
(16 * 5.7) + 11 = 102 every 1.6 seconds, 3825 max possible DPM - 94.8%<br>
<br>
Mode DPM<br>
(24 * 2) + 11 = 59 every 2.2 seconds, 1609 DPM - 99.8%<br>
(16 * 2) + 11 = 43 every 1.6 seconds, 1613 DPM - 100%<br>
<br>
Min DPM<br>
12 damage every 2.2 seconds, 327 DPM - 72.7%<br>
12 damage every 1.6 seconds, 450 DPM - 100%<br>
<br>
Now factor in the fact that paladins/SKs have about a 3-5% lower hit percentage.<br>
<br>
Max<br>
4036 * 62% hit rate = 2502 max DPM, 100%<br>
3825 * 65% hit rate = 2486 max DPM, 99.4%<br>
<br>
Mode<br>
1609 * 62% hit rate = 998 DPM, 95.2%<br>
1613 * 65% hit rate = 1048 DPM, 100%<br>
<br>
Min<br>
327 * 62% hit rate = 202 DPM, 68.9%<br>
450 * 65% hit rate = 293 DPM, 100%<br>
<br>
I wouldn't want to try and figure out what the extra 100 atk that warriors have over paladins would do as far as shifting the damage histogram upwards, so I'm not even going to try. Just be aware that the warrior has a slight advantage in that regard as well.<br>
<br>
Warriors also have a 10 point advantage in double attack, so keep in mind that double attack will be firing slightly more often for the warrior.<br>
<br>
Probably not the numbers you were expecting.<br>
<br>
The grass is not greener. <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686"> Graal MacBladefury</A><BR>
