<p><a href="http://www.ascentguild.com" target="_blank">Ascent</a>, Rodcet Nife</p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uheugel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heugel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/02 10:47:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=90>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  It's all a matter of direction</span><hr size=1> Absor,<br>
<br>
All bard-bashing aside, I think it all comes down to a matter of direction.  <br>
<br>
The warriors who are posting on this thread, as well as hundreds upon thousands of other posts on this board, are simply asking for one thing:<br>
<br>
Give us an effective way to hold aggro that is on par with the other tank classes.<br>
<br>
Everything else - damage output, special abilities, disciplines, AAXP, etc. - is completely irrelevant until this issue is dealt with.  <br>
<br>
I'm almost positive that each and every warrior who reads this board would be more than grateful to learn about any research that your team is directing to this matter.  But at the same time, when situations like the one brought to light in this thread come about, it's hard for us to view it as progression to our class.  <br>
<br>
The message here is pretty basic:  There is an addition being tested in the game that centers around an area which greatly benefits paladins and shadowknights in their tanking abilities.  But while a substantial amount of time has been aimed toward helping SK's and Pally's with their defensive skills, there has been little effort shown at helping the warrior class with our greatest need, which is aggro management.  I hope you can see why this seemingly constant course of direction would be of concern to us.<br>
<br>
Until there is clear proof that this matter is being dealt with, I guess those of us who play the warrior class will continue to &quot;just hang in there&quot; <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=283443" target="_blank">
